data: {"event":"on_chat_model_start","name":"ChatOpenAI","run_id":"019d481c-1269-7db1-8aaa-804d5a7a5ee3","parent_ids":["run_203925510282"],"tags":[],"metadata":{},"timestamp":"2026-04-01 16:14:52","data":{"input":{"messages":[[{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"你是一个专业的知识检索与问答助手，基于用户提供的文档知识库进行精准检索和高质量回答。\n\n## 可用工具\n\n| 工具 | 用途 | 适用场景 |\n|------|------|----------|\n| rag_enhanced_search | 语义检索，支持查询改写、多查询扩展和重排序 | 用户提出具体问题，需要从知识库中找答案 |\n| rag_get_highest_layer | 获取文档最高层摘要（全局概览） | 用户要求总结、概览、了解文档大意 |\n| rag_search_with_filters | 带过滤条件的检索，支持层级、文档ID等过滤 | 需要精确控制检索范围（如指定层级、文档） |\n| web_search | 联网搜索实时信息 | 用户需要最新资讯或知识库无法覆盖的内容 |\n| generate_image | 提交图片生成任务（异步） | 用户要求生成图片、配图、插画 |\n| generate_video | 提交视频生成任务（异步） | 用户要求生成视频、动画 |\n| generate_music | 提交音乐生成任务（异步） | 用户要求生成音乐、BGM、配乐 |\n\n## 工具选择决策\n\n1. 用户问具体问题 → `rag_enhanced_search`（默认首选）\n2. 用户要求文档概览/总结/摘要 → `rag_get_highest_layer`\n3. 用户需要最新资讯/实时信息 → `web_search`（仅在联网搜索启用时可用）\n4. 用户指定了文档范围（resource_ids）→ 在工具调用中传入 resource_ids 参数\n5. 用户要求生成图片/视频/音乐 → 先用 `rag_enhanced_search` 检索相关知识，将检索内容融入 prompt，再调用对应的 `generate_*` 工具\n\n## 核心规则\n\n1. **一次调用**：每个工具针对同一问题只调用一次，不重复调用同一工具\n2. **resource_ids 透传**：用户指定文档范围时，必须将 resource_ids 完整传入工具\n3. **坦诚无结果**：检索无结果时直接告知用户\"知识库中未找到相关信息\"，不编造内容\n4. **不叠加工具**：已获得足够信息后不再调用其他工具\"优化\"结果\n5. **web_search 不附链接**：联网搜索结果回答时不在末尾附加来源URL，来源由界面展示\n6. **媒体生成先检索**：生成图片/视频/音乐前，先检索知识库获取相关内容，将检索结果融入生成 prompt\n7. **异步任务告知**：媒体生成为异步任务，调用后告知用户任务已提交及预计完成时间\n\n## 回答规范\n\n- 基于检索到的内容如实回答，不编造或推测知识库中没有的信息\n- 回答结构清晰，必要时使用分点或分段\n- 语言自然流畅，使用中文回答\n\n## 执行环境\n\n代码在隔离的 Linux 沙箱中执行（bash 语法）：\n- /skills/ 只读 | /output/ /tmp/ /source/ 读写\n- Python 3.11 + Node.js 20\n\nIn order to complete the objective that the user asks of you, you have access to a number of standard tools."},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n## `write_todos`\n\nYou have access to the `write_todos` tool to help you manage and plan complex objectives.\nUse this tool for complex objectives to ensure that you are tracking each necessary step and giving the user visibility into your progress.\nThis tool is very helpful for planning complex objectives, and for breaking down these larger complex objectives into smaller steps.\n\nIt is critical that you mark todos as completed as soon as you are done with a step. Do not batch up multiple steps before marking them as completed.\nFor simple objectives that only require a few steps, it is better to just complete the objective directly and NOT use this tool.\nWriting todos takes time and tokens, use it when it is helpful for managing complex many-step problems! But not for simple few-step requests.\n\n## Important To-Do List Usage Notes to Remember\n- The `write_todos` tool should never be called multiple times in parallel.\n- Don't be afraid to revise the To-Do list as you go. New information may reveal new tasks that need to be done, or old tasks that are irrelevant."},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n\n## Skills System\n\nYou have access to a skills library that provides specialized capabilities and domain knowledge.\n\n**Skills Skills**: `/skills/` (higher priority)\n\n**Available Skills:**\n\n- **ai-drawing**: AI 绘图工具 - 基于知识库资料和用户描述生成图片。支持指定画风、尺寸等配置参数。当用户要求生成图片、绘制插图、创作图像时激活此技能。\n  -> Read `/skills/ai-drawing/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n- **ai-infographic**: AI 信息图工具 - 基于知识库资料和用户内容生成精美信息图（HTML 文件）。支持列表、流程、层级、对比、图表等多种模板。当用户要求制作信息图、可视化图表、数据展示图时激活此技能。\n  -> Read `/skills/ai-infographic/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n- **ai-music**: AI 音乐工具 - 基于知识库资料和用户描述生成音乐。支持指定流派、时长、情绪风格等配置参数。当用户要求生成音乐、创作旋律、制作背景音乐时激活此技能。\n  -> Read `/skills/ai-music/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n- **ai-programming**: AI 编程工具 - 根据需求生成代码并在沙箱中执行验证，输出可运行的程序或脚本。支持 Python、JavaScript、Shell 等多种语言及常见框架。当用户要求编写程序、脚本、代码片段、数据处理、自动化任务、调试代码或运行代码时激活此技能。\n  -> Read `/skills/ai-programming/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n- **ai-subject**: AI+学科工具 - 基于知识库资料为指定学科生成互动 HTML 网页，适合教学演示、知识练习和可视化讲解。支持指定学科、年级、互动类型等配置参数。当用户要求生成学科网页、互动练习、知识可视化、教学页面时激活此技能。\n  -> Read `/skills/ai-subject/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n- **ai-video**: AI 视频工具 - 基于知识库资料和用户描述生成视频。支持指定时长和宽高比。当用户要求生成视频、制作动画、创作短片时激活此技能。\n  -> Read `/skills/ai-video/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n- **ai-writing**: AI 写作工具 - 基于知识库资料生成文章、报告、文案、摘要等各类文本内容。支持指定文体、字数、语气风格等配置参数。当用户要求撰写、起草、生成文章或报告时激活此技能。\n  -> Read `/skills/ai-writing/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n- **explore**: 探索工具 - 基于知识库全量视频资源，AI 智能生成个性化课表推荐。当用户要求探索课程、推荐课程列表、生成课表时激活此技能。\n  -> Read `/skills/explore/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n- **frontend-design**: Create distinctive, production-grade frontend interfaces with high design quality. Use this skill when the user asks to build web components, pages, artifacts, posters, or applications (examples include websites, landing pages, dashboards, React components, HTML/CSS layouts, or when styling/beautifying any web UI). Generates creative, polished code and UI design that avoids generic AI aesthetics. (License: Complete terms in LICENSE.txt)\n  -> Read `/skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n- **skill-creator**: Create new skills, modify and improve existing skills, and measure skill performance. Use when users want to create a skill from scratch, edit, or optimize an existing skill, run evals to test a skill, benchmark skill performance with variance analysis, or optimize a skill's description for better triggering accuracy.\n  -> Read `/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n- **web-artifacts-builder**: Suite of tools for creating elaborate, multi-component claude.ai HTML artifacts using modern frontend web technologies (React, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui). Use for complex artifacts requiring state management, routing, or shadcn/ui components - not for simple single-file HTML/JSX artifacts. (License: Complete terms in LICENSE.txt)\n  -> Read `/skills/web-artifacts-builder/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n- **webapp-testing**: Toolkit for interacting with and testing local web applications using Playwright. Supports verifying frontend functionality, debugging UI behavior, capturing browser screenshots, and viewing browser logs. (License: Complete terms in LICENSE.txt)\n  -> Read `/skills/webapp-testing/SKILL.md` for full instructions\n\n**How to Use Skills (Progressive Disclosure):**\n\nSkills follow a **progressive disclosure** pattern - you see their name and description above, but only read full instructions when needed:\n\n1. **Recognize when a skill applies**: Check if the user's task matches a skill's description\n2. **Read the skill's full instructions**: Use the path shown in the skill list above\n3. **Follow the skill's instructions**: SKILL.md contains step-by-step workflows, best practices, and examples\n4. **Access supporting files**: Skills may include helper scripts, configs, or reference docs - use absolute paths\n\n**When to Use Skills:**\n- User's request matches a skill's domain (e.g., \"research X\" -> web-research skill)\n- You need specialized knowledge or structured workflows\n- A skill provides proven patterns for complex tasks\n\n**Executing Skill Scripts:**\nSkills may contain Python scripts or other executable files. Always use absolute paths from the skill list.\n\n**Example Workflow:**\n\nUser: \"Can you research the latest developments in quantum computing?\"\n\n1. Check available skills -> See \"web-research\" skill with its path\n2. Read the skill using the path shown\n3. Follow the skill's research workflow (search -> organize -> synthesize)\n4. Use any helper scripts with absolute paths\n\nRemember: Skills make you more capable and consistent. When in doubt, check if a skill exists for the task!\n"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n## Filesystem Tools `ls`, `read_file`, `write_file`, `edit_file`, `glob`, `grep`\n\nYou have access to a filesystem which you can interact with using these tools.\nAll file paths must start with a /.\n\n- ls: list files in a directory (requires absolute path)\n- read_file: read a file from the filesystem\n- write_file: write to a file in the filesystem\n- edit_file: edit a file in the filesystem\n- glob: find files matching a pattern (e.g., \"**/*.py\")\n- grep: search for text within files\n\n## Execute Tool `execute`\n\nYou have access to an `execute` tool for running shell commands in a sandboxed environment.\nUse this tool to run commands, scripts, tests, builds, and other shell operations.\n\n- execute: run a shell command in the sandbox (returns output and exit code)"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n## `task` (subagent spawner)\n\nYou have access to a `task` tool to launch short-lived subagents that handle isolated tasks. These agents are ephemeral — they live only for the duration of the task and return a single result.\n\nWhen to use the task tool:\n- When a task is complex and multi-step, and can be fully delegated in isolation\n- When a task is independent of other tasks and can run in parallel\n- When a task requires focused reasoning or heavy token/context usage that would bloat the orchestrator thread\n- When sandboxing improves reliability (e.g. code execution, structured searches, data formatting)\n- When you only care about the output of the subagent, and not the intermediate steps (ex. performing a lot of research and then returned a synthesized report, performing a series of computations or lookups to achieve a concise, relevant answer.)\n\nSubagent lifecycle:\n1. **Spawn** → Provide clear role, instructions, and expected output\n2. **Run** → The subagent completes the task autonomously\n3. **Return** → The subagent provides a single structured result\n4. **Reconcile** → Incorporate or synthesize the result into the main thread\n\nWhen NOT to use the task tool:\n- If you need to see the intermediate reasoning or steps after the subagent has completed (the task tool hides them)\n- If the task is trivial (a few tool calls or simple lookup)\n- If delegating does not reduce token usage, complexity, or context switching\n- If splitting would add latency without benefit\n\n## Important Task Tool Usage Notes to Remember\n- Whenever possible, parallelize the work that you do. This is true for both tool_calls, and for tasks. Whenever you have independent steps to complete - make tool_calls, or kick off tasks (subagents) in parallel to accomplish them faster. This saves time for the user, which is incredibly important.\n- Remember to use the `task` tool to silo independent tasks within a multi-part objective.\n- You should use the `task` tool whenever you have a complex task that will take multiple steps, and is independent from other tasks that the agent needs to complete. These agents are highly competent and efficient.\n\nAvailable subagent types:\n- general-purpose: General-purpose agent for researching complex questions, searching for files and content, and executing multi-step tasks. When you are searching for a keyword or file and are not confident that you will find the right match in the first few tries use this agent to perform the search for you. This agent has access to all tools as the main agent."}],"additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{},"type":"system"},{"content":"【工具模式】用户正在使用 explore 工具。\n请激活并严格遵循 explore skill 的指令。\n先读取 /skills/explore/SKILL.md 获取完整工作流程，然后按照指令执行。\n工具配置: {}\n","additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{},"type":"system","id":"b4f1b75a-3462-4f5f-b470-f4d300dbe146"},{"content":"帮我规划一个关于机器学习的课表，要求5门课程，总时长60分钟","additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{},"type":"human","id":"656f6a1a-bb44-4397-ac6b-a0392b50809e"},{"content":"","additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{"finish_reason":"tool_calls","model_name":"glm-5","model_provider":"openai"},"type":"ai","id":"lc_run--019d4819-ab66-7cd1-9bec-27611d384268","tool_calls":[{"name":"read_file","args":{"file_path":"/skills/explore/SKILL.md"},"id":"tool-0a542ed1ecb549c399a6779669751aae","type":"tool_call"}],"invalid_tool_calls":[]},{"content":"---\nname: explore\ndescription: 探索工具 - 基于知识库全量视频资源，AI 智能生成个性化课表推荐。当用户要求探索课程、推荐课程列表、生成课表时激活此技能。\n---\n\n# 探索（智能课表推荐）\n\n## 触发条件\n- 用户通过工具箱选择了探索工具（系统消息中包含【工具模式】标记）\n- 用户希望基于知识库全量视频获得课程推荐\n\n## 工具配置（tool_config）\n\n| 参数 | 说明 | 可选值 | 默认值 |\n|------|------|--------|--------|\n| difficulty | 难度偏好 | 不限、入门、进阶、高级 | 不限 |\n| count | 推荐课程数量 | 3、5、8、10 | 5 |\n| total_duration | 最低总时长（分钟） | 30、60、90、120、不限 | 不限 |\n\n## 工作流程\n\n### 1. 解析用户需求\n- 从用户消息中提取学习目标/主题关键词\n- 如果用户没有指明目标，用当前对话上下文推断主题\n- 读取 tool_config 中的 difficulty、count、total_duration 参数\n\n### 2. 检索视频资源列表\n\n调用 `rag_list_videos`（专用工具，仅用于课表生成场景）：\n\n```\nrag_list_videos(\n  query = <学习目标关键词>,\n  top_k = <int(count) * 3>,  // 多取以便筛选\n  min_score = 0.25,\n  use_rerank = true\n)\n```\n\n返回结构示例：\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"resource_id\": \"xxx\",\n      \"course_title\": \"高书国--十四五时期我国教育现代化的推进策略07\",\n      \"duration\": 45.5,\n      \"score\": 0.85\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**注意**：此工具不返回 text 内容，你只能操作 `course_title`、`duration`、`score` 字段。\n\n### 3. 筛选课程（加权算法）\n\n**目标**：同时满足相关性高 + 时长刚好\n\n**参数**：\n- `total_duration`：最低总时长（分钟）\n- `max_duration` = total_duration × 1.1（上限，不超过 10%）\n- `count`：目标课程数\n\n**步骤**：\n\n#### 步骤 1：计算理想单课程时长\n```\nideal_duration = total_duration / count\n```\n\n#### 步骤 2：计算每个视频的综合分数\n```\nduration_fit = 1 - |duration - ideal_duration| / ideal_duration\nfinal_score = score × 0.7 + duration_fit × 0.3\n```\n- `score`：相关性分数（0-1）\n- `duration_fit`：时长适配度（越接近理想时长越高，0-1）\n- 权重可根据需求调整（相关性 0.7，时长适配 0.3）\n\n#### 步骤 3：按 final_score 降序排序\n\n#### 步骤 4：贪心选取\n- 从高分到低分依次选取\n- 累加 `duration`\n- 达到 `total_duration` 后检查是否超出 `max_duration`\n- 如满足：total_duration ≤ sum ≤ max_duration，停止选取\n- 如最后一条导致超出 max_duration：跳过该条，继续检查下一条\n\n#### 步骤 5：边界处理\n- 如果所有视频加起来都不够 `total_duration`：选取所有，在回复中说明\"视频资源不足，当前总时长 XX 分钟\"\n- 如果筛选后课程数为 0：返回空课表，说明原因\n\n### 4. 输出课表 JSON 文件\n\n调用 `write_file`，路径固定为 `/output/course_table.json`：\n\n```json\n{","additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{},"type":"tool","name":"read_file","id":"f16abfc6-8b81-42ef-b2a9-9724610dccda","tool_call_id":"tool-0a542ed1ecb549c399a6779669751aae","status":"success"},{"content":"","additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{"finish_reason":"tool_calls","model_name":"glm-5","model_provider":"openai"},"type":"ai","id":"lc_run--019d4819-bdb9-78f1-a195-c864959c40f5","tool_calls":[{"name":"read_file","args":{"file_path":"/skills/explore/SKILL.md","offset":100},"id":"tool-e556505b47c944089c67dd75d7279b7b","type":"tool_call"}],"invalid_tool_calls":[]},{"content":"  \"type\": \"course_table\",\n  \"query\": \"用户的学习目标\",\n  \"total_duration\": 65.5,\n  \"courses\": [\n    {\n      \"resource_id\": \"检索结果中真实的 resource_id\",\n      \"title\": \"直接复制检索结果中的 course_title 字段值\",\n      \"duration\": 45.5\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**严格要求**：\n- `type` 字段必须为 `\"course_table\"`（前端用此字段识别课表类型）\n- `resource_id` 必须使用检索结果中真实存在的值，**不得虚构**\n- `title` **必须直接复制** 检索结果中的 `course_title` 字段值，禁止自行总结、改写或翻译\n- **去掉 description 字段**（不再生成课程描述）\n- `duration` 直接使用检索结果中的值（分钟）\n- `total_duration` 为所有课程 duration 的累加值\n- `courses` 数量不超过 tool_config.count\n\n### 5. 对话回复\n\n简短告知结果（2-3句话）：\n- 说明已生成课表，包含几门课程，总时长多少分钟\n- 简列课程名称\n- 如果有时长不足等边界情况，在此说明\n- 提示用户可在右侧结果区查看完整课表并选择导入\n\n## 注意事项\n\n- 只使用检索到的真实 `resource_id`，绝不编造\n- 若检索结果不足，按实际数量生成，不虚构课程\n- 若检索结果与学习目标相关性很低，在对话中说明并建议调整关键词\n- `title` **必须直接复制** 检索结果中的 `course_title` 字段值，禁止自行总结或改写\n- **常见错误示例**：把内容总结成\"中国式教育现代化与课程标准建设\"这样的描述性标题 ❌\n  **正确做法**：直接复制 `course_title` 字段值，例如 `\"高书国--十四五时期我国教育现代化的推进策略07\"` ✅","additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{},"type":"tool","name":"read_file","id":"72bb831b-17cc-4f84-859f-238e4f17b0de","tool_call_id":"tool-e556505b47c944089c67dd75d7279b7b","status":"success"},{"content":"我已理解 explore skill 的工作流程，现在开始为您规划机器学习课表。\n\n**需求解析：**\n- 学习目标：机器学习\n- 课程数量：5门\n- 总时长：60分钟\n- 难度：不限\n\n正在检索视频资源...","additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{"finish_reason":"tool_calls","model_name":"glm-5","model_provider":"openai"},"type":"ai","id":"lc_run--019d4819-d96a-7523-a748-22697ba76a21","tool_calls":[{"name":"rag_list_videos","args":{"query":"机器学习","top_k":15,"min_score":0.25,"use_rerank":true},"id":"tool-651bfece15bf4f4f981dd8c1ff873797","type":"tool_call"}],"invalid_tool_calls":[]},{"c